Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature5_update_after_close_ignored:
{
  "description": "Once the container has been closed, any further update request is silently ignored: the current value is left unchanged. A subscriber that attaches after closing is delivered only the final value followed immediately by a completion signal. Output shows the unchanged value read after the ignored update, then the late subscriber's summary.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "initial": 0,
        "steps": [
          {
            "op": "close"
          },
          {
            "op": "increase"
          },
          {
            "op": "read"
          },
          {
            "op": "subscribe",
            "id": "a"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "state=0\nsubscriber=a values=[0] done=true\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature4_value_update_after_subscribe:
{
  "description": "Delivery of values to a subscriber happens asynchronously, after the current synchronous turn completes. When the value is updated one or more times synchronously right after subscribing (within the same turn, before delivery begins), those intermediate updates collapse and the subscriber's first delivered value is the resulting latest value rather than the value present at the moment of subscription. The subscriber then observes completion when the container closes.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "initial": 0,
        "steps": [
          {
            "op": "subscribe",
            "id": "a"
          },
          {
            "op": "increase"
          },
          {
            "op": "close"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "subscriber=a values=[1] done=true\n"
    }
  ]
}

Here are the authoritative public test cases for feature3_broadcast_multiple_subscribers:
{
  "description": "The container is a broadcast source: it reports that it supports broadcasting and permits multiple independent subscribers at the same time. Each subscriber attached before the container closes is delivered the current value and its own completion signal. Output is the broadcast capability line followed by one summary line per subscriber, in attachment order.",
  "cases": [
    {
      "input": {
        "initial": 0,
        "steps": [
          {
            "op": "broadcast"
          },
          {
            "op": "subscribe",
            "id": "a"
          },
          {
            "op": "subscribe",
            "id": "b"
          },
          {
            "op": "close"
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected_output": "broadcast=true\nsubscriber=a values=[0] done=true\nsubscriber=b values=[0] done=true\n"
    }
  ]
}

